fields.description:
The Web Python course will allow you to master the Python programming language and understand its fundamental aspects: modules, parsers, and regular expressions. The course is aimed at helping you learn how to create efficient programs to solve your tasks. It will teach you to develop your own web applications for working with databases and websites. You'll be able to use Python to learn Java, Ruby, PHP, C, C++, C#, or any other programming language.
The Web Python course covers the study of web frameworks like Django, Bootstrap, and Flask.
In the second semester, you will learn tools and methods such as:

* PHP and MySql;
* Working with DOC, EXCEL, PATH files;
* Relational and object-oriented database model;
* Package creation and management;
* How to work with an FTP server;
* Environment setup and website creation;
* Web servers;
* Configuration management in Unix and Windows;
* Tools for website creation;
* Integration of external applications;
* Extensions;
